Teva CEO Says MS Pill Could Become ‘Blockbuster,’ Globes Reports

-- B y   N a o m i   K r e s g e
-- 
2011-04-12T15:24:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/teva-ceo-says-ms-pill-could-become-blockbuster-globes-reports.html
Teva Pharmaceutical Industries
Ltd. (TEVA) ’s multiple sclerosis pill laquinimod could become a so-
called blockbuster drug with $1 billion in annual sales,  Globes 
reported, citing Chief Executive Officer Shlomo Yanai.  The experimental medicine could be a blockbuster alongside
Teva’s existing MS therapy Copaxone, the Israeli newspaper
quoted Yanai as saying at a conference in  Tel Aviv  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Naomi Kresge in Berlin at 
